HEADWORD: Cadmia
<hw>Cad"mi*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>cadmia</ets>
calamine, Gr. <?/. Cf. <er>Calamine</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>An oxide of zinc which collects on the sides of furnaces where zinc
is sublimed. Formerly applied to the mineral
<xex>calamine</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

